@startuml
!theme plain

title E2E Coordinator Session and Peer State Model

[*] --> SessionCreated

SessionCreated --> CoordinatorStarting : config parsed
CoordinatorStarting --> CoordinatorReady : server bound
CoordinatorStarting --> Failed : cannot bind host/port

CoordinatorReady --> BuildingTests : build-for-testing or sample launch
BuildingTests --> XcTestRunPrepared : .xctestrun patched
BuildingTests --> Failed : build failed

XcTestRunPrepared --> LaunchingPeers : peer plan ready

state LaunchingPeers {
  [*] --> PeerPending
  PeerPending --> PeerStarting : start condition satisfied
  PeerStarting --> PeerConnecting : process launched
  PeerConnecting --> PeerRunning : websocket hello/welcome
  PeerConnecting --> PeerFailed : handshake timeout
  PeerStarting --> PeerFailed : launch failed
  PeerRunning --> PeerWaiting : wait predicate requested
  PeerWaiting --> PeerRunning : event observed
  PeerWaiting --> PeerFailed : timeout
  PeerRunning --> PeerReconnecting : socket closed
  PeerReconnecting --> PeerRunning : reconnect with lastSeenSeq\nand replay events
  PeerReconnecting --> PeerFailed : reconnect timeout
  PeerRunning --> PeerPublishing : emit event
  PeerPublishing --> PeerRunning : publish receipt accepted/enqueued/sent/acked
  PeerPublishing --> PeerFailed : delivery barrier timeout
  PeerRunning --> PeerFinished : test process exits 0
  PeerRunning --> PeerFailed : test process exits non-zero
  PeerFinished --> [*]
  PeerFailed --> [*]
}

LaunchingPeers --> CollectingArtifacts : all peers finished
LaunchingPeers --> Failed : any required peer failed

CollectingArtifacts --> Succeeded : summary written
CollectingArtifacts --> Failed : required artifact missing

Succeeded --> [*]
Failed --> [*]

note right of LaunchingPeers
  Peer ids and names are assigned
  by the runner and injected via
  test environment values.
end note

note bottom of PeerWaiting
  Waits are event predicates,
  not fixed sleeps.
end note

@enduml
